# Personal Life Tracker - Next.js App

A premium, dark-mode personal life tracker to manage goals across **Gym**, **Learning**, and **Content Creation** categories — with progress visualization, streak tracking, and local storage persistence.

## Proposed Changes

### Project Setup

#### [NEW] Next.js project at `C:\Users\bikas\.gemini\antigravity\scratch\life-tracker`
- Initialize with `npx create-next-app@latest` (App Router, no Tailwind, JavaScript)
- Install `react-icons` for iconography

---

### Design System & Layout

#### [NEW] `src/app/globals.css`
- CSS custom properties for dark theme (deep navy/indigo palette with neon accent gradients)
- Glassmorphism utility classes, card styles, animated progress bars
- Google Font: **Inter** for clean modern typography
- Smooth micro-animations and hover transitions

#### [NEW] `src/app/layout.js`
- Root layout with sidebar navigation + main content area
- Links: Dashboard, Gym, Learning, Content Creation

#### [NEW] `src/components/Sidebar.js`
- Fixed left sidebar with icon+label navigation, active state highlighting, glassmorphism background

---

### Pages

#### [NEW] `src/app/page.js` — Dashboard
- Overview cards showing total goals, completion %, and streaks per category
- Animated circular progress rings per category
- Recent activity feed

#### [NEW] `src/app/gym/page.js` — Gym Goals
- Track workouts: exercise name, sets, reps, weight, completion status
- Weekly workout calendar view
- Add/edit/delete goals via modal

#### [NEW] `src/app/learning/page.js` — Learning Goals
- Track topics/courses: title, resource link, progress %, status (Not Started / In Progress / Completed)
- Progress bars per item

#### [NEW] `src/app/content/page.js` — Content Creation Goals
- Track content pieces: title, platform (YouTube, Blog, Twitter, etc.), status (Idea / Drafting / Published)
- Kanban-style columns for status visualization

---

### Shared Components

| Component | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `GoalCard.js` | Reusable card with title, progress, actions |
| `ProgressRing.js` | Animated SVG circular progress |
| `AddGoalModal.js` | Modal form for adding/editing goals |
| `StatsCard.js` | Dashboard stat card with icon + value |
| `EmptyState.js` | Friendly empty state illustration |

---

### Data & Persistence

#### [NEW] `src/lib/storage.js`
- Utility wrapping `localStorage` for CRUD operations on goals
- Separate keys per category: `gym_goals`, `learning_goals`, `content_goals`
- Auto-generate IDs with `crypto.randomUUID()`

---

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- No unit tests planned (UI-heavy app with local storage). Verification is visual.

### Browser Verification
1. Run `npm run dev` and open the app in the browser
2. Verify the dashboard renders with empty state
3. Navigate to each category page (Gym, Learning, Content)
4. Add a goal in each category and verify it persists on page refresh
5. Edit and delete a goal, confirm updates
6. Return to dashboard and verify stats update correctly

### Manual Verification
- After implementation, I will open the running app in the browser tool, navigate all pages, add/edit/delete goals, and take screenshots to confirm everything works.
